## 🐛 Bug Report

Lib version: 4.4.0

The exceljs package is not correctly hiding sheets in the generated file. Even after setting ws.state = 'hidden', the sheet remains visible when opening the file in Excel. Same issue using 'veryHidden'

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
const ExcelJS = require('exceljs');

const wb = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
const ws = wb.addWorksheet('Sheet1');
const ws2 = wb.addWorksheet('Sheet2');

ws.state = 'hidden';

wb.xlsx.writeBuffer().then((buffer) => {
    require('fs').writeFileSync('test.xlsx', buffer);
    console.log('File saved!');
});;
```

## The expected behaviour:

When opening PolicyCategory.xlsx in Excel, the type sheet should be hidden. However, it remains visible.

